\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces True and conformal safety bounds in 3D, zoomed onto a single obstacle. The solid blue ball is the \emph  {true} safety boundary $D_{t+i}(x)=r_{\mathrm  {safe}}$ around the actual obstacle (used only for evaluation); the translucent red shell is the \emph  {conformal lower-bound} boundary $\underline  {D}_{t+i\mid t}(x)=r_{\mathrm  {safe}}$ obtained from the functional conformal prediction, i.e.\ the nominal safety region around the predicted center inflated by the margin. The conformal surface encloses the true one, certifying coverage, and the executed FCP-MPC path (green) threads just outside it---progressing efficiently while respecting the worst-case safety constraint. Faint gray spheres are other obstacles in the scene.}}{14}{figure.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:fcp_3d}{{6}{14}{True and conformal safety bounds in 3D, zoomed onto a single obstacle. The solid blue ball is the \emph {true} safety boundary $D_{t+i}(x)=r_{\mathrm {safe}}$ around the actual obstacle (used only for evaluation); the translucent red shell is the \emph {conformal lower-bound} boundary $\underline {D}_{t+i\mid t}(x)=r_{\mathrm {safe}}$ obtained from the functional conformal prediction, i.e.\ the nominal safety region around the predicted center inflated by the margin. The conformal surface encloses the true one, certifying coverage, and the executed FCP-MPC path (green) threads just outside it---progressing efficiently while respecting the worst-case safety constraint. Faint gray spheres are other obstacles in the scene}{figure.6}{}}
