\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {7}{\ignorespaces Closed-loop trajectory comparison in the dense 3D quadrotor task ($M{=}280$ dynamic obstacles) across three random seeds, shown in panels~(a)--(c). Each panel overlays all four controllers---CC-MPC (gray), ECP-MPC (orange), ACP-MPC (purple), and FCP-MPC (ours, blue). Green square: start; black star: goal; a red~$\times $ marks where a controller lost control and fell to the floor. FCP-MPC is the only method that makes consistent progress to the goal across seeds, while the baselines stall or crash early in the dense field.}}{15}{figure.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:traj_3d}{{7}{15}{Closed-loop trajectory comparison in the dense 3D quadrotor task ($M{=}280$ dynamic obstacles) across three random seeds, shown in panels~(a)--(c). Each panel overlays all four controllers---CC-MPC (gray), ECP-MPC (orange), ACP-MPC (purple), and FCP-MPC (ours, blue). Green square: start; black star: goal; a red~$\times $ marks where a controller lost control and fell to the floor. FCP-MPC is the only method that makes consistent progress to the goal across seeds, while the baselines stall or crash early in the dense field}{figure.7}{}}
